Title: 1. Batman
Description: The Dark Knight of Gotham City begins his war on crime with his first major enemy being Jack Napier, a criminal who becomes the clownishly homicidal Joker.

Title: 2. Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade
Description: In 1938, after his father goes missing while pursuing the Holy Grail, Indiana Jones finds himself up against the Nazis again to stop them from obtaining its powers.

Title: 3. Lethal Weapon 2
Description: Riggs and Murtaugh are on the trail of South African diplomats who are using their immunity to engage in criminal activities.

Title: 4. Look Who's Talking
Description: After a single, career-minded woman is left on her own to give birth to the child of a married man, she finds a new romantic chance in a cab driver. Meanwhile, the point-of-view of the newborn baby is narrated through voice-over.

Title: 5. Honey, I Shrunk the Kids
Description: The scientist father of a teenage girl and boy accidentally shrinks his and two other neighborhood teens to the size of insects. Now the teens must fight diminutive dangers as the father searches for them.

Title: 6. Back to the Future Part II
Description: After visiting 2015, Marty McFly must repeat his visit to 1955 to prevent disastrous changes to 1985...without interfering with his first trip.

Title: 7. Ghostbusters II
Description: The discovery of a massive river of ectoplasm and a resurgence of spectral activity allows the staff of Ghostbusters to revive the business.

Title: 8. The Little Mermaid
Description: A mermaid princess makes a Faustian bargain in an attempt to become human and win a prince's love.

Title: 9. Driving Miss Daisy
Description: An old Jewish woman and her African-American chauffeur in the American South have a relationship that grows and improves over the years.

Title: 10. Parenthood
Description: Four Buckman siblings attempt to raise their children - each in their own different style - and deal with the joys and sorrows that the process brings.

Title: 11. Dead Poets Society
Description: Maverick teacher John Keating returns in 1959 to the prestigious New England boys' boarding school where he was once a star student, using poetry to embolden his pupils to new heights of self-expression.

Title: 12. When Harry Met Sally...
Description: Harry and Sally have known each other for years, and are very good friends, but they fear sex would ruin the friendship.

Title: 13. The War of the Roses
Description: A married couple tries everything to drive each other out of the house in a vicious divorce battle.

Title: 14. Steel Magnolias
Description: A young beautician, newly arrived in a small Louisiana town, finds work at the local salon, where a small group of women share a close bond of friendship, and welcome her into the fold.

Title: 15. National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation
Description: The Griswold family's plans for a big family Christmas predictably turn into a big disaster.

Title: 16. Turner & Hooch
Description: A detective must adopt a rambunctious dog in order to help him find a killer.

Title: 17. Born on the Fourth of July
Description: The biography of Ron Kovic. Paralyzed in the Vietnam war, he becomes an anti-war and pro-human rights political activist after feeling betrayed by the country for which he fought.

Title: 18. Uncle Buck
Description: Laid back commitment-phobe Buck babysits his brother's rebellious teenage daughter and her cute younger brother and sister.

Title: 19. Field of Dreams
Description: Iowa farmer Ray Kinsella is inspired by a voice he can't ignore to pursue a dream he can hardly believe. Supported by his wife, Ray begins the quest by turning his ordinary cornfield into a place where dreams can come true.

Title: 20. Tango & Cash
Description: Framed by their ruthless arch-nemesis, a pair of mismatched LAPD officers must put their differences aside to get even with the brutal crime baron who sent them to rot in a maximum-security prison.

Title: 21. Harlem Nights
Description: During the 1930s, a New York City illegal gambling house owner and his associates must deal with strong competition, gangsters, and corrupt cops in order to stay in business.

Title: 22. Sea of Love
Description: A detective investigating a series of murders becomes involved with a woman who may be the culprit.

Title: 23. Pet Sematary
Description: After tragedy strikes, a grieving father discovers an ancient burial ground behind his home with the power to raise the dead.

Title: 24. The Abyss
Description: A civilian diving team is enlisted to search for a lost nuclear submarine and faces danger while encountering an alien aquatic species.

Title: 25. Star Trek V: The Final Frontier
Description: Captain Kirk and his crew must deal with Mr. Spock's long-lost half-brother who hijacks the Enterprise for an obsessive search for God at the center of the galaxy.

Title: 26. Major League
Description: The new owner of the Cleveland Indians puts together a purposely horrible team so they'll lose and she can move the team. But when the plot is uncovered, they start winning just to spite her.

Title: 27. See No Evil, Hear No Evil
Description: Dave is deaf, and Wally is blind. They witness a murder, but it was Dave who was looking at her, and Wally who was listening.

Title: 28. Black Rain
Description: Two NYC cops arrest a Yakuza member and must escort him when he's extradited to Japan.

Title: 29. Always
Description: The spirit of a recently deceased expert pilot mentors a newer pilot while watching him fall in love with the girlfriend that he left behind.

Title: 30. K-9
Description: To stop an elusive criminal, a maverick detective enlists the aid of a police dog who's an unusually intelligent smart alec.

Title: 31. Three Fugitives
Description: A reformed bank robber is taken hostage by a desperate man during a bank hold up, but is forced to go on the run with his captor when they're both mistakenly thought to be in cahoots.

Title: 32. Bill & Ted's Excellent Adventure
Description: Two rock-'n-rolling teens, on the verge of failing their class, set out on a quest to make the ultimate school history report after being presented with a time machine.

Title: 33. The Karate Kid Part III
Description: Ostracised villain John Kreese attempts to gain revenge on Daniel and Miyagi, with the help of a Vietnam War comrade, the wealthy owner of a toxic waste disposal business.

Title: 34. The 'Burbs
Description: An overstressed suburbanite and his neighbors are convinced that the new family on the block is part of a murderous Satanic cult.

Title: 35. Fletch Lives
Description: After receiving an inheritance in Louisiana, Los Angeles reporter Irwin Fletcher heads to the Belle Isle plantation where he gets himself into hilarious trouble.

Title: 36. Licence to Kill
Description: A vengeful James Bond goes rogue to infiltrate and take down the organization of a drug lord who has murdered his friend's new wife and left him near death.

Title: 37. Lean on Me
Description: The dedicated but tyrannical Joe Clark is appointed the principal of a decaying inner-city school he is determined to improve by any and all means.

Title: 38. Weekend at Bernie's
Description: Two idiots try to pretend that their murdered employer is really alive, leading the hitman to attempt to track him down to finish him off.

Title: 39. Road House
Description: A legendary bouncer comes to restore order at a notorious bar but runs afoul of a ruthless crime boss who controls the town.

Title: 40. The Dream Team
Description: Four mental patients on a field trip in New York City must save their caring chaperon, who ends up being taken to a hospital in a coma after accidentally witnessing a murder, before the killers can find him and finish the job.

Title: 41. Do the Right Thing
Description: On the hottest day of the year on a street in the Bedford-Stuyvesant section of Brooklyn, everyone's hate and bigotry smolders and builds until it explodes into violence.

Title: 42. All Dogs Go to Heaven
Description: A canine angel, Charlie, sneaks back to earth from heaven but ends up befriending an orphan girl who can speak to animals. In the process, Charlie learns that friendship is the most heavenly gift of all.

Title: 43. Glory
Description: Robert Gould Shaw leads the U.S. Civil War's first all-black volunteer company, fighting prejudices from both his own Union Army, and the Confederates.

Title: 44. Sex, Lies, and Videotape
Description: A sexually repressed woman's husband is having an affair with her sister. The arrival of a visitor with a rather unusual fetish changes everything.

Title: 45. A Nightmare on Elm Street: The Dream Child
Description: The pregnant Alice finds Freddy Krueger striking through the sleeping mind of her unborn child, hoping to be reborn into the real world.

Title: 46. Dad
Description: While his mom recovers in hospital from a heart attack, John puts his busy life on hold to fly home and help his elderly dad around the house. John's son later joins them and they all truly bond for the first and, tragically, final time.

Title: 47. Lock Up
Description: With only six months left of his sentence, inmate Frank Leone is transferred from a minimum security prison to a maximum security prison by a vindictive warden.

Title: 48. Cousins
Description: Two couples go to a mutual friend's wedding and end up swapping partners.

Title: 49. Say Anything
Description: A noble underachiever and a beautiful valedictorian fall in love the summer before she goes off to college.

Title: 50. An Innocent Man
Description: After airline mechanic James Rainwood is framed by two corrupt police officers, he begins plotting his revenge against them.

Title: 51. The Fly II
Description: The almost-human son of "Brundlefly" searches for a cure to his mutated genes while being monitored by a nefarious corporation that wishes to continue his father's experiments.

Title: 52. Skin Deep
Description: A womanizing alcoholic writer, whose life seems to be falling apart at the seams, repeatedly finds himself in trouble of one sort or another with the law, ex-girlfriends, and jealous boyfriends.

Title: 53. Blaze
Description: A middle-aged Louisiana governor falls in love with a young stripper, which jeopardizes his political career and the radical policies which have made him a controversial figure.

Title: 54. Her Alibi
Description: Phil has writer's block after 30 detective novels. In court for inspiration, he sees a cute Romanian murder suspect. He provides her alibi. She stays with him. Will he live to write another novel?

Title: 55. Casualties of War
Description: During the Vietnam War, a soldier finds himself the outsider of his own squad when they unnecessarily kidnap a female villager, for their sexual enjoyment.

Title: 56. Prancer
Description: A farm girl nurses a wounded reindeer she believes is one of Santa's, hoping to bring it back to health in time for Christmas. Her holiday spirit inspires those around her, something her disheartened father is having trouble understanding.

Title: 57. The Fabulous Baker Boys
Description: The lives of two struggling musicians, who happen to be brothers, inevitably change when they team up with a beautiful, up-and-coming singer.

Title: 58. Crimes and Misdemeanors
Description: An ophthalmologist's mistress threatens to reveal their affair to his wife while a married documentary filmmaker is infatuated with another woman.

Title: 59. Shocker
Description: After being sent to the electric chair, a serial killer uses electricity to come back from the dead and carry out his vengeance on the football player who turned him in to the police.

Title: 60. Chances Are
Description: A reincarnated man unknowingly falls in love with his own daughter from his previous life. Once he realizes this, he tries to end their relationship before angels erase his memory.

Title: 61. No Holds Barred
Description: A TV-network boss pits a wrestler called Zeus against a wrestler called Rip in a wrestling match.

Title: 62. Next of Kin
Description: Truman, a Chicago cop, sets out to find the killer of his brother. Meanwhile, another of his brothers, Briar (a hillbilly) decides to find the killer himself.

Title: 63. Leviathan
Description: Perched on the hull of a wrecked Soviet freighter, a team of deep-sea miners led by head oceanographer Steven Beck comes face to face with a mutant creature that's the product of a failed genetic experiment.

Title: 64. She-Devil
Description: A surprisingly resourceful housewife vows revenge on her husband when he begins an affair with a wealthy romance novelist.

Title: 65. My Left Foot
Description: Christy Brown, born with cerebral palsy, learns to paint and write with his only controllable limb - his left foot.

Title: 66. Kickboxer
Description: Kurt Sloane must learn the ancient kick boxing art of Muay Thai in order to avenge his brother.

Title: 67. Friday the 13th Part VIII: Jason Takes Manhattan
Description: Jason Voorhees is accidentally awakened from his watery grave and ends up stalking a ship full of graduating high-school students headed to Manhattan, New York.

Title: 68. The Wizard
Description: A boy and his brother run away from home and hitch cross-country, with help from a girl they meet, to compete in the ultimate video-game championship.

Title: 69. Great Balls of Fire!
Description: The life and career of wildly controversial rock 'n' roll star Jerry Lee Lewis.

Title: 70. Family Business
Description: An ex-professor offers Adam $1,000,000 to "get" some plasmids from a high tech company's lab. Adam asks his criminal grandpa for help. Can they convince Adam's now honest dad to join?

Title: 71. Pink Cadillac
Description: Skip tracer Tommy looks for bail-jumper Lou Ann. Her crime is marrying Roy, who left counterfeit money in their mobile home and got her arrested. She leaves Roy in his pink Cadillac full of money. His psycho friends want their money back.

Title: 72. She's Out of Control
Description: When an average-looking teenage girl gets a makeover, it's enough to make her father become overprotective of her.

Title: 73. Halloween 5: The Revenge of Michael Myers
Description: One year after the events of Halloween 4: The Return of Michael Myers (1988), the Shape returns to Haddonfield once again in an attempt to kill his now-mute niece.

Title: 74. Gross Anatomy
Description: A fisherman's son goes through medical school with a bad attitude, especially in cadaver class.

Title: 75. Police Academy 6: City Under Siege
Description: Those bumbling cadets take to the streets when three inept goons successfully orchestrate a metropolitan crime wave.

Title: 76. Wild Orchid
Description: A female lawyer becomes mesmerized by a self-made millionaire during an encounter in Rio setting off a series of erotic encounters.

Title: 77. Who's Harry Crumb?
Description: Harry Crumb is a bumbling and inept private investigator who is hired to solve the kidnapping of a young heiress which he's not expected to solve because his employer is the mastermind behind the kidnapping.

Title: 78. New York Stories
Description: A middle-aged artist obsessed with his pretty young assistant, a precocious 12-year-old living in a hotel, and a neurotic lawyer with a possessive mother make up three Gotham tales.

Title: 79. The Package
Description: Experienced Green Beret sergeant Johnny Gallagher is escorting a prisoner, Airborne Ranger Thomas Boyette, back to the US, but Boyette escapes and Gallagher must risk life and limb to catch him.

Title: 80. We're No Angels
Description: Two fugitives pass themselves off as priests in the hope of evading capture and passing the police blockade at the border with Canada.

Title: 81. Cyborg
Description: A martial artist hunts a killer in a plague-infested urban dump of the future.

Title: 82. Henry V
Description: In the midst of the Hundred Years War, the young King Henry V of England embarks on the conquest of France in 1415.

Title: 83. Tap
Description: Just released from prison, Max Washington must decide which of his previous professions to return to: burglary or tap-dancing.

Title: 84. Warlock
Description: A warlock flees from the 17th to the 20th century, with a witch-hunter in hot pursuit.

Title: 85. Renegades
Description: An undercover cop forms an alliance with a Native American to help him hunt down the criminals who stole an ancient Lakota tribal lance.

Title: 86. Scandal
Description: Based on the Profumo Scandal of 1963, an affair between an exotic dancer and the Minister of War shakes up the British government.

Title: 87. True Believer
Description: A cynical former civil liberties attorney now reduced to "specializing" in defending drug dealers becomes transformed by an eight-year-old murder case.

Title: 88. Troop Beverly Hills
Description: A soon to be divorced Beverly Hills socialite is determined to prove to her husband and herself that she can finish what she starts out to do, by becoming a den mother to a troop of Beverly Hills Girl Scouts.

Title: 89. Cheetah
Description: A "born free" type story set in Kenya about an orphaned cheetah cub that is adopted and raised by an American family.

Title: 90. DeepStar Six
Description: A team of navy personnel stationed at a temporary base at the bottom of the ocean and tasked with setting up nuclear missiles discovers a huge underwater cavern which houses a giant prehistoric creature.

Title: 91. Dead Bang
Description: A man kills a storekeeper and a cop. LASD homicide detective Jerry Beck gets the case. His murder suspect is connected to a heavily armed white supremacy group.

Title: 92. Dead Calm
Description: After a tragedy, John Ingram and his wife Rae are spending some time isolated at sea, when they come across a stranger who has abandoned a sinking ship.

Title: 93. Enemies, A Love Story
Description: A ghostwriter finds himself romantically involved with his current wife, a married woman and his long-vanished wife.

Title: 94. The Cook, the Thief, His Wife & Her Lover
Description: At an opulent gourmet restaurant, a woman carries on an affair with deadly consequences.

Title: 95. Disorganized Crime
Description: Career criminal Frank plans a bank heist and sends for his buddies to help pull the job. Before his buddies arrive, he's caught, forcing his cohorts to pull the job alone. Frank soon escapes, setting off a search by the bumbling cops.

Title: 96. Johnny Handsome
Description: After being double crossed and thrown in jail, a deformed gangster gets a new face and rehabilitation, but his desire for revenge looms.

Title: 97. Relentless
Description: Two Los Angeles police detectives, cynical veteran Malloy and cocky rookie Dietz, hunt for a serial killer, an ex-cop named Taylor, who randomly chooses his victims from a phone directory.

Title: 98. Roger & Me
Description: After General Motors closes its factory in Flint, Michigan, eliminating 35,000 jobs, filmmaker Michael Moore undertakes a quixotic quest to interview General Motors' chairman, Roger B. Smith.

Title: 99. The Gods Must Be Crazy II
Description: Six people meet in the Kalahari desert: a female NYC lawyer flying with a local zoologist/pilot in a mini-plane, a Cuban and an African soldier taking each other POW, a Boer elephant poacher, and a Bushman looking for his two children.

Title: 100. Music Box
Description: A lawyer defends her father accused of war crimes, but there is more to the case than she suspects.
